text.__SUMMARY__: Malayotyphlops koekkoeki, also known commonly as Koekkoek's blind snake or the Boenjoe Island worm snake, is a species of snake in the family Typhlopidae.
text.Etymology: The specific name, koekkoeki, is in honor of Dutch scientific illustrator Marinus Adrianus Koekkoek (1873-1944).
text.Geographic range: M. koekkoeki is found on the Indonesian island of Bunyu off the northeastern coast of Borneo.
